        <div class="item-wrap">
          <div class="center-layout cf">
            <div class="item-left">
              <h2 class="title">A Modeler&#39;s Tale</h2>
              <div class="details section">
                <span>2016-06-09T06:49:04Z</span> (GMT)
                <span>
                  by
                  <span class="authors-holder">
                    
                    
                      
  
<a class="normal-link author" href=""">
  markus wolfien
</a>
                    
                      
  
<a class="normal-link author" href=""">
  andrea bagnacani
</a>
                    
                      
  
<a class="normal-link author" href=""">
  tom gebhardt
</a>
                    
                      
  
    
  
<a class="normal-link author" href="https://figshare.com/authors/_/2106580"">
  martin scharm
</a>
                    
                  </span>
                </span>
              </div>
              <div class="description section">We created the movie for the &lt;b&gt;10&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; International CellML Workshop&lt;/b&gt; June 2016 in Auckland, New Zealand.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The video shows &lt;i&gt;Researcher 1 (GMT)&lt;/i&gt;, who developed a model that may cure stupidity. He wants to share the simulation study with his collaborator &lt;i&gt;Researcher 2 (GMT+7)&lt;/i&gt; to get some feedback. However, it turns out that sharing the simulation study is not that easy and &lt;i&gt;Researcher 2 (GMT+7)&lt;/i&gt; is not able to reproduce the results of &lt;i&gt;Researcher 1 (GMT)&lt;/i&gt; using &lt;i&gt;The Simulator.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;Fortunately, &lt;i&gt;Supervisor&lt;/i&gt; comes in to help &lt;i&gt;Researcher 1 (GMT).&lt;/i&gt; He points &lt;i&gt;Researcher 1 (GMT)&lt;/i&gt; to COMBINE archives. &lt;b&gt;A COMBINE archive is a container format meant to organise and annotate all files necessary to reproduce a simulation study.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Eventually, &lt;i&gt;Researcher 1 (GMT)&lt;/i&gt; is able to transfer his late-breaking research results bundled into a COMBINE archive to &lt;i&gt;Researcher 2 (GMT+7).&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;The Simulator &lt;/i&gt;finally knows what to do, as there is now everything available and in the right place. It turns out that the model is valid and stupidity is going to cease!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Thanks&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;We would like to thank the whole Free Software Community, as most of the video was produced using Free Software! Special thanks to&lt;br&gt;* Debian GNU/Linux (debian.org)&lt;br&gt;* Cheese (wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Cheese)&lt;br&gt;* Flowblade (github.com/jliljebl/flowblade)&lt;br&gt;* Gimp (gimp.org)&lt;br&gt;* Kevin MacLeod (incompetech.com) for providing the music as CC:BY&lt;br&gt;</div>
              <div class="comments section">Comments are currently unavailable</div>
            </div>
